You're right. Here's the clean solution.

Vercel needs a config entry to serve PDFs. Open vercel.json in your GitHub repo and add this:

json
{
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*).pdf",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "Content-Type",
          "value": "application/pdf"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
If your vercel.json already has content in it, paste just the headers block into the existing JSON alongside your redirects. Commit it, wait for Vercel to redeploy, then test the URL again.

